n=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 29, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104arp1665702621651.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arp1665702621651.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arp1665702621651.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"arp1665702621651\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Provides a specific instruction to the compiler.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"arp1665702621651__topic_d93461e1_d93462e1_d93463e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arp1665702621651__p_d93464e1_d93465e1_d93466e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#pragma</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fsyntaxoverride</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arp1665702621651__section_dvh_kgd_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d954040e66\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arp1665702621651__p_d93470e1_d93471e1_d93472e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fsyntaxoverride</span>—instructs the compiler to allow the field syntax in a\n            subtype entity to override that defined in its supertype.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arp1665702621651__section_inw_mgd_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d954040e78\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arp1665702621651__p_d135212e1_d135213e1_d135214e1\">Allowed in all Uniface component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arp1665702621651__section_mtx_ngd_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d954040e87\">fsyntaxoverride</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arp1665702621651__p_d93482e1_d93483e1_d93484e1\">When a supertype entity specifies a field syntax of\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">MAN</code> (mandatory), it is not possible to change this value in its\n            subtype entities, or in components that use the subtype entities. This was possible\n            prior to Uniface 9.6.01. If this change in behavior causes problems, it is possible to\n            revert to the old behavior by using the directive <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#pragma\n               fsyntaxoverride</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"arp1665702621651__note_usq_qgd_lwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Although this directive can be set in any trigger,\n            it is strongly recommended that you set it in the Declarations container of the\n            component. This ensures that all items in the component use this setting during\n            compilation.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arp1665702621651__p_d93485e1_d93486e1_d93487e1\">When the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#pragma fsyntaxoverride</span> is\n            present, and the field syntax of the subtype entity differs from the supertype, the\n            component is compiled but a warning is issued:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"arp1665702621651__pre_wsq_qgd_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">1024 warning: Field syntax for field is overwritten on component level because fsyntaxoverride pragma is set</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3611983\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3611983\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "#pragma Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 29, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Provides a specific instruction to the compiler. #pragma fsyntaxoverride Parameters fsyntaxoverride —instructs the compiler to allow the field syntax in a subtype entity to override that defined in its supertype. Use Allowed in all Uniface component types. fsyntaxoverride When a supertype entity specifies a field syntax of MAN (mandatory), it is not possible to change this value in its subtype entities, or in components that use the subtype entities. This was possible prior to Uniface 9.6.01. If this change in behavior causes problems, it is possible to revert to the old behavior by using the directive #pragma fsyntaxoverride . Note: Although this directive can be set in any trigger, it is strongly recommended that you set it in the Declarations container of the component. This ensures that all items in the component use this setting during compilation. When the #pragma fsyntaxoverride is present, and the field syntax of the subtype entity differs from the supertype, the component is compiled but a warning is issued: 1024 warning: Field syntax for field is overwritten on component level because fsyntaxoverride pragma is set Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}